item.title: CUPCAKE CANNON
item.description:
CUPCAKE CANNON
The Johnny Cupcakes Suitcase Tour stop at Kamp Grizzly was epic. Johnny brought a great crowd, his limited edition tour gear and the inspiration for Kamp's Cupcake Cannon. Portland's Kamp Grizzly developed a steam-punk style pneumatic cupcake cannon and set the stage for eating frosty delights at 120psi. The blasting buffet was documented in at 700fps coming off the Phantom HD Gold. As the evening shook down, cupcake enthusiasts continued to step in front of the cannon and camera. Some shaking in their boots, others perched in zen-like states, ALL were covered in delicious frosting, spongy cake, and showered in a mist of sprinkles.

item.title: JBSource's EXCLUSIVE Interview with Justin Bieber
item.description:
JBSource's EXCLUSIVE Interview with Justin Bieber
Ash and I (Johanna) were lucky enough to get some time with Justin while he was down in Sydney last Monday (the 26th of April 2010)! I'm on first (white-ish top), and Ash after me (pink top). :) And, apparently, it was the first time he'd ever done something like this! We're so grateful :) OH. We only had one night to prepare. We didn't even know it was definitely happening until a few hours before. Chill out! I talk real quick. It wasn't because I was nervous. It's just how I am. Sorry if you can't understand it! Ash was really nervous too. We're just teenagers. Give us a break! ahhahaha This version is only temporary while we work on getting our high-def version up. We've had some technical difficulties with it, so it's taking a while. If needed, we'll even put subtitles on that one for you all.
